productComments.commentText:
Celebrate the 77th Anniversary of the annual Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race and saturate yourself in the competitiveness of the boating world by securing your very own front-row seat!

Enjoy boating history and the electric atmosphere watching all the action and excitement up close and personal onboard the luxury vessel MV Eye Spy!

77 

 MV Eye Spy

Feiern Sie den 77. Jahrestag des jhrlichen Brisbane-Gladstone-Yachtrennens und tauchen Sie in den Wettbewerb der Bootswelt ein, indem Sie sich Ihren ganz persnlichen Sitzplatz in der ersten Reihe sichern!

Genieen Sie Bootsgeschichte und die elektrisierende Atmosphre, whrend Sie all die Action und Aufregung hautnah an Bord des Luxusschiffs MV Eye Spy verfolgen!

Clbrez le 77e anniversaire de la course annuelle Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race et imprgnez-vous de la comptitivit du monde de la navigation de plaisance en obtenant votre propre place au premier rang!

Profitez de l'histoire de la navigation de plaisance et de l'atmosphre lectrique en regardant de prs toute l'action et l'excitation  bord du navire de luxe MV Eye Spy!

77 

 MV Eye Spy

Comemore o 77 aniversrio da corrida anual de iates de Brisbane a Gladstone e mergulhe na competitividade do mundo nutico garantindo seu prprio lugar na primeira fila!

Aproveite a histria da navegao e a atmosfera eltrica observando toda a ao e emoo de perto e pessoalmente a bordo do luxuoso navio MV Eye Spy!

Celebre el 77. aniversario de la regata anual de yates de Brisbane a Gladstone y sumrjase en la competitividad del mundo de la navegacin asegurando su propio asiento en primera fila!

Disfrute de la historia de la navegacin y de la atmsfera elctrica viendo toda la accin y emocin de cerca y en persona a bordo del barco de lujo MV Eye Spy!

Rayakan Hari Jadi ke-77 dari Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race tahunan dan jenuhkan diri Anda dalam daya saing dunia perahu dengan mengamankan kursi baris depan Anda sendiri!

Nikmati sejarah berperahu dan suasana elektrik menyaksikan semua aksi dan kegembiraan dari dekat dan pribadi di atas kapal mewah MV Eye Spy!

Festeggia il 77 anniversario dell'annuale Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race e saturati nella competitivit del mondo della nautica assicurandoti il tuo posto in prima fila!

Goditi la storia della nautica e l'atmosfera elettrizzante osservando tutta l'azione e l'eccitazione da vicino e personalmente a bordo della lussuosa nave MV Eye Spy!

-   77           !

  MV Eye Spy            !

_source.productDescription:
Get egg-cited for a cracking Easter at Redcliffe Markets! They're going all out with TWO egg-stra special market days - Good Friday & Easter Sunday! How good (Friday) is that?!

What's Hopping?

Easter Bunny Meet & Greet  Snap a selfie with the one and only Easter Bunny!

Egg-stra special Easter Scavenger Hunt- Hop by and follow a trail of clues that'll lead you on an Easter egg-scapade!

Handmade Artisan Goods: Discover handcrafted goods from local designers. From bespoke fashion to homewares, find the perfect Easter gifts and treats.

Gourmet Eats & Street Food  Feast on everything from sizzling street food to drool-worthy desserts.

Live Music & Entertainment  Groove to live tunes and soak up the lively market atmosphere with egg-citing entertainment

But that's not all! Witness the thrilling start of the iconic Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race as majestic vessels set sail on the horizon.

Hop, skip, and jump into Easter fun!

Round up your crew, bring the family, and get ready for a cracking time at Redcliffe Markets' Easter Extravaganza - it's going to be an egg-ceptional weekend!
_source.productShortDescription: Get ready for an egg-stra special Easter celebration at the Redcliffe Markets on Good Friday and Easter Sunday!

accessibilityAttributes.attributeSubType1IdDescription: Actively welcomes people with access needs.

attributes.attributeIdDescription: Offer multiple options for booking - web, email, phone
Offer a range of contact methods for receiving complaints
Accept the Companion Card
Employ people with disability
Train your staff in disability awareness
Ask all visitors if there are any specific needs to be met
Website meets WCAG 2.0 accessibility standards
Provide assistance with booking arrangements (includes providing clear  itineraries with written instructions  on what to do at various destinations)

attributeBlocks.attributeSubType2IdDescription: Welcomes and assists people who have challenges with learning, communication, understanding and behaviour. (includes people with autism, intellectual disability, Down syndrome, acquired brain injury (ABI), dyslexia and dementia)

attributes.attributeIdDescription: Train your staff in communicating with people with learning or behavioural challenges
Use Plain English / easy read signage and information (includes menus and emergency information)
A quiet space is available at the venue/ facility

attributeBlocks.attributeSubType2IdDescription: Caters for people who are blind or have vision loss.

attributes.attributeIdDescription: Provide information in large print
Provide digital communication materials (hard copy information is also available on line)
Use easy read fonts in your signage and communication materials (Helvetica and Arial)
Train your staff  in customer service for people with vision loss (training would incorporate way finding and communicating with people with vision loss)
Have an appropriate area for toileting an assistance dog
Have handrails on all your stairways
Have Exit signs which are visible at a ground level (high level signs are difficult to see in a fire)

attributeBlocks.attributeSubType2IdDescription: Caters for people who are deaf or have hearing loss.

attributes.attributeIdDescription: Train your staff in communicating with people who are deaf or have hearing loss
Have a low noise reception areas with hearing loss friendly acoustics and adequate lighting for viewing facial expressions (includes common areas which are free of background noise, background music)

attributeBlocks.attributeSubType2IdDescription: Caters for people with sufficient mobility to climb a few steps but who would benefit from fixtures to aid balance. (This includes people using walking frames and mobility aids)

attributes.attributeIdDescription: Use floors/coverings which are slip resistant, firm and smooth
Use non-slip tiles in the bathroom or slip resistant matting
Have grab rails in the bathroom
Provide seating in common areas including reception area

attributeBlocks.attributeSubType2IdDescription: Caters for people who use a wheelchair.

attributes.attributeIdDescription: Have step free outdoor pathways (includes picnic areas, barbecues and shelters)
Have a step free main entrance to the building and/or reception area (includes ramps or slopes with a maximum gradient of 1:14, otherwise are too steep for wheelchairs)
Have an accessible public toilet which is unlocked
Have a wheelchair accessible toilet / shower and change room
Have at least one wheelchair accessible parking space with wheelchair accessible signage clearly displayed (International standards are 3200mm wide x 2500 mm high)

Have wheelchair accessible transport options available in the general vicinity (provide information on name of the operator, phone and website link to individual providers for private vehicles, community transport train, mini vans, hire cars, buses, taxis, ferry, tram, light rail etc in your access statement)

attributeBlocks.attributeSubType2IdDescription: Caters for people with allergies and intolerances.

attributes.attributeIdDescription: Modify your cooking and cleaning practices to cater for people with food allergies or chemical intolerances (could include menus with meals free from: nuts, dairy, seafood, eggs, gluten etc)
Train your staff to respond to allergic reactions
Adhere to The Food Authority requirements for allergy management in food preparation

Encuentro con el Conejo de Pascua: Hazte una selfi con el inigualable Conejo de Pascua!

Bsqueda del Tesoro de Pascua especial para celebrar la Pascua! Pasa por aqu y sigue las pistas que te llevarn a una aventura de huevos de Pascua!

Productos artesanales: Descubre productos hechos a mano de diseadores locales. Desde moda a medida hasta artculos para el hogar, encuentra los regalos y dulces perfectos para Pascua.

Comida gourmet y comida callejera: Delitate con todo, desde comida callejera chispeante hasta postres para chuparse los dedos.

Msica en vivo y entretenimiento: Disfruta de la msica en vivo y sumrgete en el animado ambiente del mercado con entretenimiento emocionante.

Pero eso no es todo! Presencia el emocionante inicio de la icnica Regata Brisbane-Gladstone con majestuosas embarcaciones zarpando hacia el horizonte.

Salta, brinca y lnzate a la diversin de la Pascua!

Rene a tu tripulacin, trae a la familia y preprate para pasarlo genial en la Extravaganza de Pascua de Redcliffe Markets. Ser un fin de semana excepcional!

Freuen Sie sich auf ein fantastisches Osterfest auf den Redcliffe Markets! Gleich zwei besondere Markttage gibt es hier: Karfreitag und Ostersonntag! Wie schn ist das denn (Freitag)?

Was gibts zu erleben?

Osterhasen-Meet & Greet  Machen Sie ein Selfie mit dem einzigartigen Osterhasen!

Eine besondere Oster-Schnitzeljagd  Folgen Sie den Hinweisen und stbern Sie durch die Welt der Ostereier!

Handgefertigte Produkte: Entdecken Sie handgefertigte Produkte von lokalen Designern. Von mageschneiderter Mode bis hin zu Haushaltswaren  finden Sie die perfekten Ostergeschenke und Leckereien.

Gourmet-Essen & Streetfood  Genieen Sie alles von brutzelndem Streetfood bis hin zu kstlichen Desserts.

Live-Musik & Unterhaltung  Tanzen Sie zu Live-Musik und genieen Sie die lebendige Marktatmosphre mit aufregender Unterhaltung.

Aber das ist noch nicht alles! Erleben Sie den spannenden Start des legendren Brisbane-Gladstone-Yachtrennens, wenn majesttische Schiffe am Horizont in See stechen.

Hpfen, hpfen und springen Sie ins Ostervergngen!

Versammeln Sie Ihre Crew, bringen Sie die Familie mit und freuen Sie sich auf ein tolles Osterfest der Redcliffe Markets  es wird ein auergewhnliches Wochenende!
(Redcliffe Markets)

Prparez-vous pour des Pques inoubliables aux marchs de Redcliffe ! Ils mettent le paquet avec deux jours de march spciaux : le Vendredi saint et le Dimanche de Pques ! C'est pas mal (vendredi) !

Quoi de neuf ?

Rencontre avec le lapin de Pques  Prenez un selfie avec l'unique lapin de Pques !

Chasse au trsor spciale Pques  Passez nous voir et suivez une piste d'indices qui vous mnera  la chasse aux ufs !

Produits artisanaux faits main : Dcouvrez des produits artisanaux de crateurs locaux. De la mode sur mesure aux articles pour la maison, trouvez les cadeaux et gourmandises de Pques parfaits.

Gastronomie et cuisine de rue  Rgalez-vous de tout, de la cuisine de rue crpitante aux desserts  tomber par terre.

Musique et divertissements en direct  Dansez au rythme des concerts et imprgnez-vous de l'ambiance anime du march avec des animations endiables.

Mais ce n'est pas tout ! Assistez au dpart palpitant de l'emblmatique course de yachts Brisbane-Gladstone, tandis que de majestueux bateaux prennent la mer  l'horizon.

Plongez dans les joies de Pques!

Rassemblez votre quipage, venez en famille et prparez-vous  vivre un week-end inoubliable  l'Extravaganza de Pques de Redcliffe Markets! Ce week-end promet d'tre exceptionnel!

Preparati a una Pasqua scoppiettante ai mercatini di Redcliffe! Stanno dando il massimo con DUE giornate di mercato speciali a tema egg-stra: Venerd Santo e Domenica di Pasqua! Quanto  bello (venerd)?!

Cosa c' di interessante?

Incontro con il coniglietto pasquale: scatta un selfie con l'unico e solo coniglietto pasquale!

Caccia al tesoro speciale di Pasqua Egg-stra: passa e segui una serie di indizi che ti condurranno a una scappatella a caccia di uova di Pasqua!

Prodotti artigianali fatti a mano: scopri prodotti artigianali di stilisti locali. Da moda su misura a articoli per la casa, trova i regali e le leccornie pasquali perfetti.

Cibo gourmet e cibo da strada: deliziati con tutto, dal cibo da strada sfrigolante ai dessert da leccarsi i baffi.

Musica dal vivo e intrattenimento: scatenati con la musica dal vivo e immergiti nella vivace atmosfera del mercato con intrattenimento egg-citing

Ma non  tutto! Assisti all'emozionante inizio dell'iconica Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race mentre maestose imbarcazioni salpano all'orizzonte.

Salta, salta e tuffati nel divertimento pasquale!

Raduna il tuo equipaggio, porta la famiglia e preparati per un momento strepitoso all'Extravaganza pasquale di Redcliffe Markets: sar un weekend eccezionale!

Bertemu & Bertemu Kelinci Paskah  Ambil swafoto dengan satu-satunya Kelinci Paskah!

Perburuan Telur Paskah yang sangat istimewa - Mampir dan ikuti jejak petunjuk yang akan membawa Anda pada petualangan telur Paskah!

Barang-barang Buatan Tangan: Temukan barang-barang buatan tangan dari desainer lokal. Dari mode yang dipesan khusus hingga peralatan rumah tangga, temukan hadiah dan suguhan Paskah yang sempurna.

Kuliner Lezat & Makanan Kaki Lima  Nikmati mulai dari makanan kaki lima yang lezat hingga hidangan penutup yang menggiurkan.

Musik & Hiburan Langsung  Nikmati alunan musik langsung dan nikmati suasana pasar yang meriah dengan hiburan yang sangat menarik

Namun, itu belum semuanya! Saksikan awal yang mendebarkan dari Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race yang ikonik saat kapal-kapal megah berlayar di cakrawala.

Lompat, lompat, dan lompat ke dalam keseruan Paskah!

Kumpulkan kru Anda, ajak keluarga, dan bersiaplah untuk bersenang-senang di Redcliffe Markets' Easter Extravaganza - ini akan menjadi akhir pekan yang luar biasa!

The Gladstone Ports Corporation Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race returns for its 77th year, setting sail on Good Friday, 18 April 2025. Hosted by the Queensland Cruising Yacht Club (QCYC), this iconic offshore race challenges sailors across a 308 nautical mile course from Brisbane to Gladstone.

First held in 1949, the race has grown into one of the country's most recognised ocean races. It has earned national and international attention while remaining a proud Queensland tradition.

Join thousands of spectators along the Moreton Bay shoreline or Shorncliffe Pier for a front row seat to the race start. The fleet begins two miles east of the pier, navigating through Moreton Bay and north along the coast to the finish at Gladstone Harbour.

At the heart of the competition is the Courier Mail Cup, one of Australia's oldest perpetual trophies. Presented to the IRC Overall Winner, it remains one of the most highly regarded prizes in Australian offshore sailing.

The race finish coincides with the Easter in Gladstone festivities. Crews, families and visitors come together to celebrate with entertainment, food and community events across the Easter weekend.

Das Gladstone Ports Corporation Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race findet zum 77. Mal statt und sticht am Karfreitag, dem 18. April 2025, in See. Ausgerichtet vom Queensland Cruising Yacht Club (QCYC), fordert dieses legendre Hochseerennen Segler auf einer 308 Seemeilen langen Strecke von Brisbane nach Gladstone heraus.

Das erstmals 1949 ausgetragene Rennen hat sich zu einem der bekanntesten Hochseerennen des Landes entwickelt. Es hat nationale und internationale Aufmerksamkeit erlangt und ist gleichzeitig eine stolze Tradition in Queensland geblieben.

Schlieen Sie sich Tausenden von Zuschauern an der Kste der Moreton Bay oder am Shorncliffe Pier an und erleben Sie den Start des Rennens in der ersten Reihe. Die Flotte startet drei Kilometer stlich des Piers, navigiert durch die Moreton Bay und Richtung Norden entlang der Kste bis zum Ziel im Hafen von Gladstone.

Im Mittelpunkt des Wettbewerbs steht der Courier Mail Cup, eine der ltesten ewigen Trophen Australiens. Er wird dem IRC-Gesamtsieger verliehen und ist nach wie vor einer der angesehensten Preise im australischen Hochseesegeln.

Das Rennende fllt mit den Osterfeierlichkeiten in Gladstone zusammen. Mannschaften, Familien und Besucher kommen am Osterwochenende zusammen, um mit Unterhaltung, Essen und Gemeinschaftsveranstaltungen zu feiern.

Verfolgen Sie das Rennen live  Zuschauer knnen das Rennen vom Shorncliffe Pier und der Kste der Moreton Bay aus verfolgen oder es live auf Kayo Freebies, Facebook, Instagram und YouTube streamen.

A Gladstone Ports Corporation Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race retorna para seu 77 ano, zarpando na Sexta-feira Santa, 18 de abril de 2025. Organizada pelo Queensland Cruising Yacht Club (QCYC), esta icnica corrida offshore desafia os velejadores em um percurso de 308 milhas nuticas de Brisbane a Gladstone.

Realizada pela primeira vez em 1949, a corrida se tornou uma das corridas ocenicas mais reconhecidas do pas. Ela ganhou ateno nacional e internacional, mantendo-se uma orgulhosa tradio de Queensland.

Junte-se a milhares de espectadores ao longo da costa de Moreton Bay ou do Per Shorncliffe para um assento na primeira fila para a largada da corrida. A frota comea duas milhas a leste do per, navegando pela Baa de Moreton e ao norte ao longo da costa at a chegada no Porto de Gladstone.

No centro da competio est a Courier Mail Cup, um dos trofus perptuos mais antigos da Austrlia. Apresentado ao Vencedor Geral do IRC, continua sendo um dos prmios mais conceituados na vela offshore australiana.

A chegada da corrida coincide com as festividades da Pscoa em Gladstone. Equipes, famlias e visitantes se renem para celebrar com entretenimento, comida e eventos comunitrios durante o fim de semana da Pscoa.

Assista  corrida ao vivo - Os espectadores podem assistir  ao do Shorncliffe Pier e da costa de Moreton Bay ou transmiti-la ao vivo no Kayo Freebies, Facebook, Instagram e YouTube.

nase a los miles de espectadores a lo largo de la costa de la baha de Moreton o del muelle de Shorncliffe para disfrutar de un asiento en primera fila desde la salida de la regata. Gladstone Ports Corporation Brisbane to Gladstone Yacht Race kembali digelar untuk tahun ke-77, berlayar pada Jumat Agung, 18 April 2025. Diselenggarakan oleh Queensland Cruising Yacht Club (QCYC), lomba lepas pantai ikonik ini menantang para pelaut melintasi jalur sepanjang 308 mil laut dari Brisbane ke Gladstone.

Pertama kali diadakan pada tahun 1949, lomba ini telah berkembang menjadi salah satu lomba laut paling terkenal di negara ini. Lomba ini telah mendapatkan perhatian nasional dan internasional sekaligus menjadi tradisi Queensland yang membanggakan.

Bergabunglah dengan ribuan penonton di sepanjang garis pantai Moreton Bay atau Dermaga Shorncliffe untuk mendapatkan tempat duduk di barisan terdepan saat lomba dimulai. Armada ini memulai perjalanan sejauh dua mil di sebelah timur dermaga, berlayar melalui Moreton Bay dan ke utara di sepanjang pantai hingga mencapai garis finis di Pelabuhan Gladstone.

Inti dari kompetisi ini adalah Courier Mail Cup, salah satu piala tertua di Australia. Diberikan kepada Pemenang Umum IRC, piala ini tetap menjadi salah satu hadiah yang paling dihormati dalam pelayaran lepas pantai Australia.

Akhir lomba bertepatan dengan perayaan Paskah di Gladstone. Para kru, keluarga, dan pengunjung berkumpul untuk merayakan dengan hiburan, makanan, dan acara komunitas selama akhir pekan Paskah.

Saksikan lomba secara langsung - Penonton dapat menyaksikan aksinya dari Dermaga Shorncliffe dan garis pantai Moreton Bay atau melakukan streaming langsung di Kayo Freebies, Facebook, Instagram, dan YouTube.
